source.name: Final Critical Habitat for the Little Colorado spinedace (Lepidomeda vittata)
source.description: Abstract: provide the user with a general idea of areas where final critical habitat for Little Colorado spinedace (Lepidomeda vittata) occur based on the description provided in the Federal Register. The geographic extent includes Apache, Coconino and Navajo Counties, Arizona.     Purpose: Critical habitat are areas considered essential for the conservation of a listed species. These areas provide notice to the public and land managers the importance of these areas to the conservation of this species. Special protections and/or restrictions are possible in areas where federal funding, permits, licenses, authorizations, or actions occur or are required.
